Dorsal axial chaetom of Th.II–Abd.III as 8–9,5–7/555–6. Thorax usually without ventral axial chaetae but one of the 
paratypes
has 1+1 ventral chaetae on Th.III. Macrochaetae clearly differentiated (
Fig. 161, 168
). Abd.V with 8 straight and thickened dorsal macrochaetae (
Fig. 161
), about 0.6 as long as tergite. Abd.IV with 4 macrochaetae on each side, dorsal and anterior ones are subequal with lateral and dorsolateral (
Fig. 168
). Sensilla on tergites clearly differentiated, significantly shorter and thinner than ordinary chaetae, microsensilla almost of the same size as sensilla (
Fig. 162, 163
). Sensillar formula 33/22224 (s), 11/111 (ms) (
Fig. 168
). Sensilla on Abd.I–III in mid-tergal position. Medial and lateral pairs of sensilla on Abd.V similar in size and set in a line (
Fig. 161
).

Dorsal axial chaetom of Th.II–Abd.III as 8–9,5–7/555–6. Thorax without ventral chaetae. Macrochaetae differentiated laterally on Th.II–III and on abdominal tip. Medial macrochaetae on Abd.V 0.4–0.5 as long as tergite. Abd.IV with 4 macrochaetae on each side. Dorsal and anterior macrochaetae are 2/3 as long as the lateral and dorsolateral (
Fig. 176
). Sensilla on tergites clearly differentiated, significantly shorter and thinner than ordinary chaetae. Microsensilla almost of the same size as sensilla. Sensillar formula 33/ 22224 (s), 11/111 (ms) (
Fig. 176
). Sensilla on Abd.I–III in mid-tergal position. Medial pair of sensilla (accp1 and accp2) on Abd.V clearly longer than lateral one (accp3 and accp4) (
Fig. 174
).
